name: Rob Smith
title: CEO at LIteracy Shed and Chair at Education Shed (Ed Shed)
user_generated_headline: CEO at LIteracy Shed and Chair at Education Shed (Ed Shed)
summary:
Founder of The Literacy Shed and Co-Founder of Education Shed.

Following over a decade as a classroom teacher and middle leader, I wanted to reach more classrooms than those in my school.  Blogging about film and images in the classroom became www.literacyshed.com.  The original Literacy Shed website is a curated collection of short films and animations to inspire writing and discussions.

Literacy Shed Plus is a collection of reading and writing resources for teachers with 1000s of schools and teachers around the world making downloads every day.

In addition to creating and managing these two sites, I also co-founded Spelling Shed, Maths Shed and the new Phonics Shed which all come under the EdShed umbrella.

member_experience_collection.title: Founder
member_experience_collection.description:
Rob Smith has been teaching in Primary schools for almost 10 years and he is currently a KS2 and Literacy Leader at a large primary school in North Manchester.

Rob's teaching and the search for innovative methods led him to use videos to inspire writing. The first animation he used with children was 'The Piano,' after this both he and the children were hooked. He began blogging his ideas and experiences with image and short film.

The blog soon developed into The Literacy Shed, somewhere to escape to and share ideas. Since going live in June 2011 the Literacy Shed has had 2.5 million visitors from over 150 different countries.

Rob is now visiting schools to deliver writing workshops to children and sharing his ideas with staff about engaging children with visual media to improve their literacy skills.
